H1.text: The profile starts from zero velocity.

H2.text: We have entered the correct result for you.

H3.text: You can use external hand calculation from application input data to compute the required value.

H4.text: Use Move Distance and segment times to compute the required value.

H5.text: Use formula =Move Distance/(((Seg 1 time+Seg3 time)/2)+Seg2 time).

H6.text: The correct answer is 150 revs/second. We have entered the number for you

H8.text: The correct value is 150 – the same as the Initial velocity. We have entered the value for you.

H9.text: This segment decelerates to a halt.

H10.text: You should have entered zero. We have entered it for you.

H12.text: You should have entered zero. We have entered it for you.

H13.text: Use a formula, involving the total of the squares of acceleration and the total time.

H14.text: The formula is the square root of the totals of the square of acceleration divided by the total time).

H15.text: You should have entered =SQRT(G7/D7). We have entered it for you.

H16.text: This is the same as the final velocity of the previous motion segment. Enter a cell formula.

H17.text: We have entered the formula for you. For example you should have entered =C3 in cell B4.

H18.text: Use a formula, involving velocity and time.

H20.text: We have entered the formula for you. You should have entered =(final velocity - initial velocity) / segment duration. For example =(C3-B3)/D3 in cell E3

H21.text: Use a formula, involving velocity and time.

H22.text: The formula is (average velocity x time, ((u+v)/2 x t).

H23.text: We have entered the formula for you. You should have entered =(initial velocity + final velocity)/ 2 * segment duration. For example =((B3 + C3)/2)*D3 in cell F3

H24.text: Use a formula, involving acceleration and time.

H25.text: The formula is the square of acceleration x time, (a2 x t).

H26.text: We have entered the formula for you. You should have entered square of acceleration * segment duration. For example =(E3^2)*D3 in cell G3.
